21/05/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- A group of Montenegrin members of parliament met with Albanian Parliament Speaker Jozefina Topalli on Tuesday (May 20th) during an official visit to Tirana, as part of Montenegro's European Movement co-operation project. "It is important that the natural regional co-operation be more intensive, especially in joint aims towards the European perspective," Topalli said. Montenegrin lawmakers briefed her on an initiative to create a co-operation network between two countries in the fields of politics and the media, which she welcomed. (TopNews, BalkanWeb, Telegrafi - 20/05/08)
